name: UNC_C_CLOCKTICKS
description: Uncore cache clock ticks

name: UNC_C_LLC_LOOKUP.ANY
description: All LLC Misses (code+ data rd + data wr - including demand and prefetch)

name: UNC_C_LLC_VICTIMS.M_STATE
description: M line evictions from LLC (writebacks to memory)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: LLC misses - demand and prefetch data reads - excludes LLC prefetches

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: LLC misses - Uncacheable reads (from cpu)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: MMIO reads

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: MMIO writes

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: LLC prefetch misses for RFO

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: LLC prefetch misses for code reads

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: LLC prefetch misses for data reads

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: LLC misses for PCIe read current

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: ItoM write misses (as part of fast string memcpy stores) + PCIe full line writes

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE
description: PCIe write misses (full cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE
description: PCIe writes (partial cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE
description: L2 demand and L2 prefetch code references to LLC

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE
description: Streaming stores (full cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE
description: Streaming stores (partial cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE
description: PCIe read current

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE
description: PCIe write references (full cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_OCCUPANCY.MISS_OPCODE
description: Occupancy counter for LLC data reads (demand and L2 prefetch)

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.READS
description: read requests to home agent

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.READS_LOCAL
description: read requests to local home agent

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.READS_REMOTE
description: read requests to remote home agent

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.WRITES
description: write requests to home agent

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.WRITES_LOCAL
description: write requests to local home agent

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.WRITES_REMOTE
description: write requests to remote home agent

name: UNC_H_SNOOP_RESP.RSPCNFLCT
description: Conflict requests (requests for same address from multiple agents simultaneously)

name: UNC_H_SNOOP_RESP.RSP_FWD_WB
description: M line forwarded from remote cache along with writeback to memory

name: UNC_H_SNOOP_RESP.RSPIFWD
description: M line forwarded from remote cache with no writeback to memory

name: UNC_H_SNOOP_RESP.RSPS
description: Shared line response from remote cache

name: UNC_H_SNOOP_RESP.RSPSFWD
description: Shared line forwarded from remote cache

name: UNC_M_CAS_COUNT.RD
description: read requests to memory controller

name: UNC_M_CAS_COUNT.WR
description: write requests to memory controller

name: UNC_M_CLOCKTICKS
description: Memory controller clock ticks

name: UNC_M_POWER_CHANNEL_PPD
description: Cycles where DRAM ranks are in power down (CKE) mode

name: UNC_M_POWER_CRITICAL_THROTTLE_CYCLES
description: Cycles all ranks are in critical thermal throttle

name: UNC_M_POWER_SELF_REFRESH
description: Cycles Memory is in self refresh power mode

name: UNC_M_PRE_COUNT.PAGE_MISS
description: Pre-charges due to page misses

name: UNC_M_PRE_COUNT.RD
description: Pre-charge for reads

name: UNC_M_PRE_COUNT.WR
description: Pre-charge for writes

name: UNC_Q_CLOCKTICKS
description: QPI clock ticks

name: UNC_Q_TxL_FLITS_G0.DATA
description: Number of data flits transmitted

name: UNC_Q_TxL_FLITS_G0.NON_DATA
description: Number of non data (control) flits transmitted

name: UNC_P_CLOCKTICKS
description: PCU clock ticks. Use to get percentages of PCU cycles events.

name: UNC_P_POWER_STATE_OCCUPANCY.CORES_C0
description: This is an occupancy event that tracks the number of cores that are in C0.  It can be used by itself to get the average number of cores in C0, with threshholding to generate histograms, or with other PCU events and occupancy triggering to capture other details.

name: UNC_P_POWER_STATE_OCCUPANCY.CORES_C3
description: This is an occupancy event that tracks the number of cores that are in C3.  It can be used by itself to get the average number of cores in C0, with threshholding to generate histograms, or with other PCU events and occupancy triggering to capture other details.

name: UNC_P_POWER_STATE_OCCUPANCY.CORES_C6
description: This is an occupancy event that tracks the number of cores that are in C6.  It can be used by itself to get the average number of cores in C0, with threshholding to generate histograms, or with other PCU events

name: UNC_P_PROCHOT_EXTERNAL_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that we are in external PROCHOT mode.  This mode is triggered when a sensor off the die determines that something off-die (like DRAM) is too hot and must throttle to avoid damaging the chip.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_LIMIT_THERMAL_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when temperature is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_OS_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when the OS is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_POWER_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when power is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_TRANS_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when current is the upper limit on frequency.
